title: What song always makes you happy? - Quora

response.answer_text: Fatboy Slim: Praise You This always makes me laugh out loud when coupled with the music video. A year ago I bought a DVD set of Spike Jonze’s music videos and short films among which was a very strange one of a chap dancing alone on the street to some music or other, making a complete ass of himself while passers-by tried not to notice. There was also Torrance Rises, about one of the most technically sloppy dance troupes ever assembled, the Torrance Community Dance Group. They were led by Richard Coufey who turned out to be the same bloke Jonze had filmed dancing alone. Many of you would already know the story behind the Praise You video, but I’m a classical music dork so all this was completely new to me. This was an “Official Music Video” and I wanted to crack up at how bad the dancing was; at the same time I thought I’d better take it a little seriously just in case there was some I-don’t-know-what happening here that I wasn’t modern enough to understand - some new dance modality or postmodernist aesthetic I was completely unfamiliar with. Or were they novices worthily breathing life into what little they’d read or seen of Isadora Duncan or the Gurdjieff movements? I recognised them both in there - very distantly - in which case the dance group deserved all the praise they could get, which would probably be very little considering they were taking on something esoteric and making a dog’s breakfast of it. Anyway, I found out ‘Richard Coufey’ was Jonze himself and that he’d masterminded the whole shebang, winning three awards at the 1999 MTV Video Music Awards as Coufey before letting the Jonze cat out of the bag! Now I’m free to crack up as much as I want to, which is a lot, every time I see it! Thanks to Being John Malkovich and Adaptation I already knew Jonze was a brilliant comedian, but I had no idea what he looked like in person. Now he’s even higher up there among the funniest, most absurd and iconoclastic comedians I know of. Knowing he’s also the tender and sensitive beating heart behind Her blows me away even further. What a guy! I’m madly in love with him!
